latestPosts.caption:
Pre-recorded files from when I was pregnant and keeping it private 🥹🙏🏼

I decided to “hide” this pregnancy from my socials because, truthfully, I just wasn’t ready to share. After losing my baby boy Franchesco last year at 20 weeks, I felt deep in my heart that if I were ever blessed to get pregnant again, I’d want to keep it between me and my closest family and friends.

I didn’t know for how long—but it just never felt right to share until the very day she was born. We also waited until I was about 15 weeks along to tell family and friends. I found out I was pregnant at 4 weeks.

My fiancé has been my rock through it all—the good, the bad, the ugly, and the really ugly. He’s carried us with so much grace, and I’m so grateful to have him by my side as my life partner 🥹♥️ @iamjasonperez 

I’m so thankful to God for this miracle and for trusting me once again to carry and bring life into this world. I’m beyond grateful to be a mommy, and even with all the ups and downs, I wouldn’t have it any other way. Everything happens for a reason, even if it takes us a long time to understand it.

And to everyone who follows me—thank you for being there through every chapter of my life and for always showing me so much love and support ♥️✨🫶🏻

Girl mom x3 💅🏻✨👗👛👑💐🎀

Thank you god for choosing me to be their  mommy 🧸🥹💞

latestPosts.caption:
✨ OUR MIRACLE STORY ✨
Aubrey Marie Perez ❤️

Only God knows how much we prayed for this pregnancy. A year ago we lost our baby boy Franchesco at 22 weeks… and it broke us. I buried myself in work to deal with the pain, but seeing Sharleen suffer crushed me.

I believe God makes no mistakes. When life gets heavy, I don’t ask “Why me?” — I ask “What is this teaching or protecting me from?”

Fast forward a year, we found out we were pregnant again — with a baby girl 👶🏽💖 At 22 weeks, Sharleen started bleeding. We rushed to the hospital… same fears, same trauma. Doctors said her water broke and we had 2 options: terminate or risk the NICU with no promises.

But I wasn’t giving up. I asked everyone to step out. I told Sharleen we’re going to pray the rosary. I dropped to my knees and cried out to God for 45 mins. I begged Him: “Please don’t let this happen again. Please save our daughter.”

Then I felt this overwhelming heat through my body and I heard the words “Tu fe te ha salvado” — your faith has saved you. I turned to Sharleen and said “Everything is going to be okay.”

I told the doctors to redo the test. They looked at me crazy — 2 tests already said positive. But I insisted.

Test 3: Inconclusive
Test 4: One negative, one positive
Test 5: Fluids looked good — they sent us home 🙌🏽

And now, on July 9th, our baby girl is HERE. Healthy. Beautiful. Strong.

AUBREY MARIE PEREZ — Daddy loves you. You are our answered prayer. You’re proof God is real. You’re our miracle.

Franchesco — thank you for watching over your little sister ❤️
God — thank You for this blessing
